The federal lawmaker representing Ezza North/Ishielu Federal Constituency in the National Assembly, Anayo Edwin, on Saturday, declared intention to contest for governorship on the platform of the Peoples Democratic party, PDP, come 2023. Edwin, a two time member of the House of Representatives, said he is prepared to rescue the state from the ruling All Progressives Congress, APC. The lawmaker, who addressed stakeholders and delegates that hail from the 13 local government areas of the state, said his administration, if elected, will be anchored on 8-point agenda. According to him: “Our administration will be anchored on 8-point agenda focused on good governance, economic growth, restoration of peace and security and social investment. “We shall also prioritize education, health and wellbeing, Agriculture, strengthening of the civil service and local government systems and infrastructure and industrial development,” he stated.